00:00:13.049 --> 00:00:14.730
to eat something

00:00:14.730 --> 00:00:17.369
khatta meeta that too using three

00:00:17.369 --> 00:00:19.350
different beans so today we're going to make

00:00:19.350 --> 00:00:23.160
Khatti meeti teen ratan so for this we're going

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:27.570
to use garbanzo, green peas and moong,

00:00:27.570 --> 00:00:30.300
green moong that is green gram so we're

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:32.610
going to use all three and use lot of

00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:35.160
tomato tamarind and make a nice khatta meeta

00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:39.480
curry so to make this teen ratan khatti

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:42.300
meeth curry add some oil in a pan, add

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:45.539
crushed garlic, add fenugreek seeds just

00:00:45.539 --> 00:00:47.730
little because this can make it bitter

00:00:47.730 --> 00:00:51.780
and add kalonji ah this kalonji has a

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:55.110
nice aroma once this is slightly cooked

00:00:55.110 --> 00:00:58.620
add chopped onion, add curry leaves, once

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:01.230
the onions are slightly sweated

00:01:01.230 --> 00:01:05.159
add pinch of salt, turmeric and now add

00:01:05.159 --> 00:01:06.299
the beans

00:01:06.299 --> 00:01:08.670
we're going to first add garbanzo that

00:01:08.670 --> 00:01:10.799
is the kabuli chana and then

00:01:10.799 --> 00:01:14.700
green peas you know these garbanzo,

00:01:14.700 --> 00:01:16.740
green peas as well as green moong

00:01:16.740 --> 00:01:18.990
I've soaked them over night and boiled them

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:21.869
separately till they're nice and tender now

00:01:21.869 --> 00:01:24.420
we're going to just saute them little

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:28.140
bit now after you saute these two then

00:01:28.140 --> 00:01:29.640
last we're going to add the green moong

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:33.060
all these three have been nicely boiled

00:01:33.060 --> 00:01:34.829
till they're nice and tender so you

00:01:34.829 --> 00:01:37.170
don't need to cook that much but you

00:01:37.170 --> 00:01:39.270
know sauteing in this oil give them a

00:01:39.270 --> 00:01:43.979
nice flavor ,in this add chili powder

00:01:43.979 --> 00:01:47.850
and depends on how spicy you want you

00:01:47.850 --> 00:01:51.030
can add chilli powder add garam masala

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:53.939
powder look at this already they're

00:01:53.939 --> 00:01:55.140
looking awesome

00:01:55.140 --> 00:01:57.689
this is what I call the teen ratan this

00:01:57.689 --> 00:01:59.820
is going to be nice and dry preparation

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:02.070
but very tasty

00:02:02.070 --> 00:02:06.960
now in this add chopped tomato just you

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:10.500
know chop them small and add to this and

00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:11.380
in this

00:02:11.380 --> 00:02:14.440
add jaggery this is what is going to

00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:16.660
give the sweetness and add some

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:20.440
tamarind juice and now you know keep

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:22.480
cooking until all this moisture

00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:25.390
evaporates and this become slightly dry

00:02:25.390 --> 00:02:27.100
now look at this

00:02:27.100 --> 00:02:29.830
the gravy the sauce that was there is

00:02:29.830 --> 00:02:33.010
evaporated and all these beans have been

00:02:33.010 --> 00:02:35.890
nicely coated with this khatmeet sauce

00:02:35.890 --> 00:02:39.400
also we cooked this beans in the oil

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:41.350
little bit some of the beans are still

00:02:41.350 --> 00:02:43.750
crunchy, dear friends now this is all

00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:44.440
done

00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:46.960
switch off the flame and top it off with

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:50.500
some chopped coriander and serve this with

00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:53.620
phulka, chapati and I'm telling you

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:57.760
huh hmm

